casebody.data: Benj. Sutherland agt. The Barquantine Lady Maunsell. This case, which was one where the owners of the vessel resided in a foreign country, and the libel instituted by a material man here to enforce a lien in rem, was decided by the same judge, and the same principle established as to such liens, as in the above case, of Whitlock agt. The Barque Thales. B. T. Sawyer, for libellant. D. McMahon, for claimant. [NO OPINION]
